@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<div class="container mt-5">
    <!-- Page Header -->
    <section class="text-center mb-5">
        <h1 class="display-4 fw-bold">Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="lead text-secondary">Your privacy is important to us. Read on to understand how EZO Inventory handles your data responsibly and securely.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- Privacy Policy Content -->
    <section class="mb-5">
        <div class="card shadow-sm">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
                <p>EZO Inventory collects information that you provide directly when using our platform, including account details, contact information, and usage data. We also collect certain information automatically, such as IP address, browser type, and access times, to enhance your experience and improve our services.</p>

                <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
                <p>Your data helps us provide a more customized experience by improving software functionality and support. We also use your information to secure your account, send necessary updates, and offer insights into your inventory management.</p>

                <h2>3. Data Security</h2>
                <p>We prioritize the security of your data by implementing stringent security measures and encryption techniques. Access to personal information is limited to authorized personnel only, and we continually review our security protocols to prevent unauthorized access.</p>

                <h2>4. Data Sharing</h2>
                <p>We do not share your personal information with third parties without your consent, except as necessary for service provision, legal compliance, or safety assurance. Third-party service providers are bound by data protection obligations to ensure your data remains secure.</p>

                <h2>5. Your Choices and Rights</h2>
                <p>You have the right to access, update, or delete your personal information at any time. To manage your preferences, please contact our support team, and we will assist you with any changes.</p>

                <h2>6. Updates to Our Policy</h2>
                <p>We may occasionally update this privacy policy to reflect changes in technology, law, or our business practices. Any updates will be communicated promptly on this page, so you remain informed.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Contact Information Section -->
    <section class="text-center py-5 bg-light rounded">
        <h2>Have Questions?</h2>
        <p class="lead text-secondary">If you have any questions about our privacy practices, feel free to reach out to us.</p>
        <a href="@Url.Action("Contact", "Home")" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Contact Support</a>
    </section>
</div>
